 <body>
  <h1>
   <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Movement/i_Movement_Set_Point_Direction.png"/><br/>
   Set Point Direction
  </h1>
  This action is used to set a direction from a vector formed by the current position of the instance and the position given. You supply the x and y position to "point" at - these can be flagged as relative to the instance position - and the
    direction from the instance to that point will be used for the instance.
  <h4>
   Action Syntax:
  </h4>
  <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Movement/a_Movement_Set_Point_Direction.png"/><br/>
  <h4>
   Arguments:
  </h4>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      x
     </td>
     <td>
      The x component of the direction vector.
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      y
     </td>
     <td>
      The y component of the direction vector.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <br/><img src="https://gms.magecorn.com/Manual/assets/Images/Scripting_Reference/Drag_And_Drop/Reference/Movement/e_Movement_Set_Point_Direction.png"/><br/>
  The above action block code checks checks to see if an instance of the object
    "
  <span>
   obj_Player
  </span>
  " exists in the room and if it does it then sets the direction of the instance to point towards the x/y position of "
  <span>
   obj_Player
  </span>
  ".
 </body>
</html>